I‚Äôm a Master of Computational Data Science student at the Language Technologies Institute, Carnegie Mellon University. I completed my Bachelor‚Äôs degree in Computer Science and Engineering at PES University.
My research interests are broadly efficieny and fidelity in machine learning. I am currently working with Prof.¬†Emma Strubell on ways to reuse parameters while growing and fine-tuning models. I am also working with Prof.¬†Yonatan Bisk on evaluating the semantic understanding capabilities of text-to-image generation models.
Last winter/spring, I interned at Apple India, where I worked on few-shot multi-label classification of error logs. Prior to that, I worked on various projects including pseudocode to code generation, emotion-guided music generation, time-series forecasting of disease spread, reinforcement learning for traffic signal control, and graph-based semi-supervised learning. You can find a list of my publications and my resume.
I believe in the power of visual storytelling and teaching. I enjoy making study notes and I was awarded by PES University‚Äôs Department of Computer Science and Engineering for my immense contributions. Feel free to check out my notes! They are categorized by subject ‚Äì most of them are CS subjects, but some are math/science.
I learn to play the South-Indian instrument Saraswathi Veena in the Carnatic style. I also enjoy cooking and baking quite a bit. I occasionaly enjoy making YouTube videos about my experiences and interests. You can check out my YouTube channel if it interests you!

title: Vibha Masti
text:
News

December 2023: Attending my first NeurIPS to present at the Machine Learning for Audio Workshop!
August 2023: Officially started my first Fall semester at the Language Technologies Institute at Carnegie Mellon University!
July 2023: I wrote a Medium article on How I Scored a 330+ on the GRE.
January 2023: I started my 6-month spring internship/co-op at Apple to work on Applied ML! I am so excited for this experience and unbelievably grateful.
December 2022: I volunteered for the ISMIR 2022 conference in Bangalore, India from 4th to 9th December 2022.
September 2022: I attended the ECML-PKDD 2022 conference in Grenoble, France with my teammates to present at the MLG workshop. Check out my vlog on it!
